n of shadowed solids can explain the elemental abundance\npatterns of the Jovian atmosphere even if proto-Jupiter was formed near\nJupiter's current orbit. The disk shadow may play a vital role in controlling\natmospheric compositions. The effect of the shadow also impacts the\ninterpretation of upcoming observations of exoplanetary atmospheres by JWST.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 16 Jun 2021 18:57:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-07-07"}
